snippet.textDisplay:
Thank you so much for a message like this Mark!
As someone who is severely immunocompromised, I often feel helpless in keeping myself healthy. It gets scary when kids in my school purposely cough in my face as a 'joke' to get my reaction, because they don't really know how serious it can be for me to even get the flu, nevermind a virus like this.
I feel bittersweet as I'm glad that governments and the media are trying to lower the panic, but I'm also let down because in trying to calm panic, they have minimised the problem to the point where people don't believe the seriousness and end up being careless. A lot of them think that sneezing or coughing on people who are already concerned about the virus is just a joke that can get them to stop worrying so much, but most of them don't realise that many of those people have a legit reason to panic. And in coughing or sneezing on them, you are directly putting them in the line of fire for any disease to make them sick and weaken them before they even have the chance of catching the virus. AND if they do catch the virus, they won't stand a chance since they're already sick.
I'm really glad that you are bringing up these topics and making people aware. Immunocompromised people are more common than expected (with 1 in 500 Americans having immune problems already, excluding acquired immune problems from HIV or cancer etc.) and there are many of us in your community. Sending these kinds of messages can really help us.


We are just trying to survive like everyone else, we just have a harder time doing it.


Please stay safe and be aware of those around you <3
*if you want to learn more about people who suffer from immune problems, there are lots of websites on the internet that can help out :)*

snippet.authorDisplayName: That One Kid We All Know
snippet.textDisplay:
All of Cornwall (County in England/UK) aren't closing their schools, we've been told by teachers that at the most they will just extend our Easter holiday. I'm honestly not worried about the Corona virus, as a fifteen year old in a wealthy country such as England, if I get the Corona virus I won't be at any risk of pain or death. My brother is what scares me, he had Colitis which is a disease that affects his immune system, a common cold can be so risky to him when he has what's known as a flare up that he has to be given steroids to be okay again. If he gets the Corona virus it won't just be a simple quarantine, he could die.
The fear of hurting him or passing this to him worries me and the knowledge that everyone is loved by someone the way I love my brother makes me do everything in my power to be hygienic so that the brothers, sisters and others of the world won't have to be in a hospital hoping for a cure.
Remember, the flu was a massive worry, now it's just a simple injection, Cancer used to be a definite death, now there's hope. There will always be a chance to be better and this will pass, or we will advance medicine to beat this.
Everything is gonna be fine
